Gareth Bale could miss out on Real Madrid's game with Rayo Vallecano after injuring his left foot during a training session on Tuesday morning.

Carlo Ancelotti's side face their second La Liga game in four days when they travel to the Estadio de Vallecas on Wednesday evening to take on ninth-placed Rayo.

But Bale, who scored Real's first goal in their 9-1 demolition of Granada on Sunday, is now a doubt according to his manager.

