Ancelotti said: 'Bale has a bang to his left foot, we must weigh it up tomorrow, then pick the team.'

The former Tottenham star was pictured taking part in training at the club's Valdebebas training ground on Tuesday but he appears to have been injured while preparing for Real's next match.

Castilla players Martin Odegaard and Alfonso Herrero were also called up for the session with the senior squad, although both players are unlikely to be involved on Wednesday.  

